# Clustering Stability in Healthcare Data

This project evaluates how distance metric selection impacts clustering stability using  
k-medoids clustering and bootstrap resampling.

## Methods
- Distance metrics: Euclidean, Manhattan, Cosine, Jaccard
- Evaluation: Adjusted Rand Index (ARI)
- Data: BRFSS (subset)

## Key Finding
Jaccard distance produced the most stable and reproducible clustering results.

## Files
- Notebook: INFO_523_Adamst_Final_Project_V18.ipynb
- Supporting data files included

## Dataset
- the BRFSS dataset cannot be uploaded to Github because it's too large < 1GB.
- The BRFSS dataset is available at https://www.cdc.gov/brfss/annual_data/2024/files/LLCP2024XPT.zip
